  "prompt": "Someone deleted me on snapchat, so I deleted him & now he appears in my Added me section, but I cannot see his score. Does this mean he added me back?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're experiencing some changes in your Snapchat connections, and it's understandable to want clarity on what's happening. Let's break down what's likely going on:\n\n### **Understanding Snapchat's \u201cAdded Me\u201d Section**\n\n1. **When Someone Adds You:**\n   - **Notification:** If someone adds you on Snapchat, they appear in your \"Added Me\" section.\n   - **Pending Status:** Until you accept their request, they remain in this section. Once accepted, they move to your friends list.\n\n2. **Deleting Each Other:**\n   - **Mutual Deletion:** If both you and the other person delete each other, it's akin to removing a friend from both ends. This means neither of you remains on the other's friends list.\n   - **Reappearance:** If either party decides to add the other again, they'll show up in the \"Added Me\" section as a new friend request.\n\n### **Regarding the Missing Snapscore**\n\n- **Snapscore Overview:** Your Snapscore reflects your Snapchat activity, including the number of snaps you've sent and received, stories you've posted, and other interactions.\n\n- **Possible Reasons for Missing Snapscore:**\n  1. **Privacy Settings:** The other user might have adjusted their privacy settings to hide their Snapscore from others. Snapchat allows users to control who can see their score.\n  2. **Account Issues:** If the person has deactivated their account or is experiencing technical issues, their Snapscore might not display properly.\n  3. **New Connection:** If they've recently added you back, there might be a temporary glitch or delay in displaying all their information, including the Snapscore.\n\n### **Does This Mean They Added You Back?**\n\n- **Likely Scenario:** If the person now appears in your \"Added Me\" section after you both deleted each other, it **could** mean they have sent you a friend request again. However, the absence of their Snapscore alone doesn't definitively confirm this action.\n\n- **Steps to Take:**\n  1. **Check Friendship Status:** Navigate to your friends list to see if they've moved from \"Added Me\" to \"Friends.\" This transition typically indicates a mutual addition.\n  2. **Await Confirmation:** Sometimes, updates take a short while to reflect accurately on the app. Give it some time to see if more details, like the Snapscore, appear.\n  3. **Reach Out Directly:** If appropriate, consider sending them a message or reaching out through another platform to confirm the connection status.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Update the App:** Ensure that your Snapchat app is updated to the latest version. Outdated versions can sometimes cause display issues.\n  \n- **Clear Cache:** Occasionally, clearing the app's cache can resolve glitches that prevent certain information from displaying correctly.\n\n- **Contact Snapchat Support:** If the issue persists and you believe it's a technical problem, reaching out to Snapchat's support team might provide a solution.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile the appearance of the person in your \"Added Me\" section suggests they might have taken steps to reconnect, the missing Snapscore isn't a definitive indicator on its own. It's best to combine this observation with the steps mentioned above to gain a clearer understanding of your current connection status on Snapchat.\n\nIf you have any more questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
